text.section:
As used in this section:
"Bill of lading" means a document evidencing the purchase of, or delivery order for, building materials issued by a person engaged in a business that sold or leased the building materials;
"Building materials" means equipment or materials associated with new home construction, home remodeling, or home maintenance, including but not limited to:
Agriculture products;
Asphalt;
Concrete;
Crushed stone;
Excavation equipment;
Fill dirt and rock;
Glass;
Landscaping materials;
Lumber or other wood products;
Minerals;
Roofing materials; and
Steel products;
"Home" means:
A site where a single or multi-family housing unit is being initially constructed; and
A site where construction of a single or multi-family housing unit is complete and persons inhabit the housing unit; and
"State road" means a state or federal highway but does not mean an interstate or county road.
